sed West Midlands Devolved Rail Franchise. This Devolution proposal covers a wider geographical area than the 25 mile restriction. This Devolution proposal reflects the current economic geography and Travel to Work Area of the West Midlands. As </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Pteg</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> stated to the House of Commons Transport Committee in 2010, the removal of the unnecessary </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">25 mile burden would be welcome. This would also allow Centro to operate outside its current </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">boundary and continue successful partnership working with Shire Authorities outside of the current 25 mile restrictions.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Centro, believe that there would be major benefits arising from this Bill, to passengers and the economy in the West Midlands, as it would: </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 1.85pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Support economic growth by delivering more capacity and connectivity</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 1.85pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Deliver a better service for passengers, encouraging use and reducing carbon emissions</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 1.85pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12p